data.value: SBSI is currently the market leader for electrophoresis testing in the Philippines and one of the top three players in Clinical Hematology and Coagulation. With its introduction of the National Institutes of Health-approved G-6PD confirmation test through its Pentra 400 chemistry instrument, it is now posing itself as a strong challenger in the medium-sized market in Clinical Chemistry.

data.name: LabelControl20.Text
data.value: SBSI’s products are mainly laboratory instruments (semi-automated to fully-automated) and their corresponding consumables. They are intended to automate and revolutionize the manual laboratory procedures into amazing technological innovations. data.name: LabelControl19.Text
data.value: The headquarters of SBSI, which provides products and after-sales support to North Luzon, South Luzon and the National Capital Region, is strategically based in Metro Manila. Its Visayas operations are based in Cebu City and Iloilo City. The Mindanao operations are based in Davao City and Cagayan de Oro City. Operationally, the company is divided into three departments: sales, service, and logistics. The sales department which is composed of twenty five Registered Medical Technologists, Biologists, Engineers and Nurses is responsible the development of various products and market in their respective territories; the service team which is composed of fifteen Registered Electrical Engineers and Electronics and Communications Engineers provides maintenance and technical support to more than 500 installed instruments all over the Philippines. Currently, its new corporate strategic direction in the next three years is to expand its market reach both in scope of territories and in terms of product mix in its portfolio.

data.name: LabelControl18.Text
data.value: SBSI has been operating for about eighteen (18) years in the Philippine diagnostics market. It has been one of the leading local diagnostics companies at the helm of developing innovative diagnostics products for hospitals and free standing laboratories all over the Philippines in the fields of hematology, immunology and clinical chemistry.

data.name: LabelControl1.Text
data.value: SCIENTIFIC BIOTECH SPECIALTIES INC. (SBSI), a company focused in in-vitro diagnostics testing, the target market of which spans the whole Philippines. It has been dedicated to helping develop an excellent diagnostics healthcare system in the Philippines by relentlessly looking for affordable and most recent innovations in in-vitro diagnostics and introducing them in the country.
